The article is a statement from the Vice President on the passing of Eunice Kennedy Shriver. The Vice President expresses sadness at her passing and highlights her energy and spirit. He mentions that she revealed a family secret about her sister Rosemary's intellectual disability and wrote about it in The Saturday Evening Post. He praises her for starting summer camps for young people with intellectual disabilities and for founding the Special Olympics. He also mentions her marriage of 56 years and her commitment to service, which she passed on to her children. The Vice President expresses gratitude for her lasting gifts and offers condolences to her family.